This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it discusses the robustness of machine learning models and proposes an algorithm to improve the generation of adversarial examples. It may also belong to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) as it discusses attacks on models and defense mechanisms. Additionally, the paper mentions computer vision (cs.CV) as a potential application area for the proposed algorithm. The use of Bayesian Optimization (BO) and Successive Halving (SH) also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
